        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:56PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rockingham, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Hamlet, Hoffman, Dobbins Heights, McFarlan, Diggs, East
Rockingham, Sandhills Game Land, and Blewett Falls Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
